title: Periodically sample user-space stack sizes
name: stack_sizes.stp
version: 1.0
author: William Cohen
keywords: memory
subsystem: memory
status: production
exit: user-controlled
output: sorted-list
scope: system-wide
description: The stack_sizes.stp script periodically samples the stack size of each process created while it is running. When the script exits a logarithmic histogram will be printed for each executable tallying the number number of times each stack size was observed for the executable.
test_check: stap -gp4 stack_sizes.stp
test_installcheck: stap -g stack_sizes.stp -T 1
